== Overview ==

Under the {{ill|Ritsuryō system|ja|律令制|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ritsuryō system|qq=}}, 大初位 was further divided into two sub-Ranks: 大初位上 (Daishoi-jō) and 大初位下 (Daishoi-ge). The Rank corresponded to positions such as the clerks of certain bureaus, {{ill|Dazaifu|ja|大宰府|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dazaifu|qq=}}'s 判事大令史 (senior clerks), 一品家少書吏 (junior scribes for first-Rank families), 二品家大書吏 (senior scribes for second-Rank families), 職事一位家少書吏 (junior scribes for first-Rank families in official roles), and the 少属 (junior assistants) of the {{ill|Kabu-ryō|ja|掃部寮|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabu-ryō|qq=}}.

In the early {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}}, distinctions between the upper and lower sub-Ranks were abolished. Furthermore, 大初位 lost its corresponding offices under the {{ill|Shokuinryō|ja|職員令|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokuinryō|qq=}} of {{ill|August 22, 1869|ja|1869th year 8月22日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/August 22, 1869|qq=}}.<ref group="notes">The Cabinet Records Bureau's "Independent Book: Meiji Official Ranks History, Section on Offices" (National Archives of Japan ref.A07090183000) states it was established on {{ill|July 8 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar July8日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 8 (Lunisolar)|qq=}} and revised on {{ill|August 20 (Lunisolar)|ja|Lunisolar August20日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/August 20 (Lunisolar)|qq=}}.</ref><ref>[{{NDLDC|787949/168}} 法令全書「明治2nd year 」], National Diet Library.</ref>

In the honors system established by the {{ill|Joi Jōrei|ja|叙位条例|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Joi Jōrei|qq=}} (Imperial Edict No. 10 of 1887) and later the {{ill|Ikai-ryō|ja|位階令|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikai-ryō|qq=}} (Imperial Edict No. 325 of 1926), no equivalent to this Rank was included.

